:"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Groom was born in 1466, in Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England. She married John Wyncoll about 1490, in Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1524, in her hometown, at the age of 58, and was buried in Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1466–1524":"1466–1524","1455–1521":"1455–1521","1491–1544":"1491–1544","1493–1531":"1493–1531","1495–1559":"1495–1559","1497–Male":"1497–Surnud","1504–1580":"1504–1580","about 1490":"umbes 1490","1495":"1495","1493":"1493","1580":"1580","1491":"1491","1524":"1524","1544":"1544","1466":"1466","1521":"1521","1455":"1455","1531":"1531","1497":"1497","about 1497":"umbes 1497","about 1495":"umbes 1495","about 1493":"umbes 1493","1504":"1504","1 November 1521":"1. november 1521","1559":"1559","Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England":"Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England","Clopton, Suffolk, England":"Clopton, Suffolk, England","LIttle, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1466–1524":"1466–1524","1455–1521":"1455–1521","1491–1544":"1491–1544","1493–1531":"1493–1531","1495–1559":"1495–